    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory corruption in turbo decoder beta computation\n\n### Summary\nThe 8-bit turbo decoder in the PHY layer exhibits memory corruption during the beta metric computation phase. When processing certain frame lengths, the `compute_beta8` function incorrectly initializes specific lanes of the beta metrics array, leading to out-of-bounds memory accesses and corrupted decoder output.\n\nThe issue manifests as incorrect LLR values during turbo decoding, particularly when `offset8_flag` is set to 0. This causes CRC failures in downlink transport channels and can lead to UE connection drops.\n\nRoot cause is a logic bug in `compute_beta8` where the `beta_ptr` assignment occurs after the conditional initialization of specific vector lanes, causing the initialization to be immediately overwritten. This results in uninitialized memory being used in subsequent computations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/3gpplte_turbo_decoder_sse_8bit.c`: Reordered `beta_ptr` reassignment to occur before conditional lane initialization in the main processing loop. Updated comment to reflect proper initialization flow.\n\n"
}